{{Quote|All they killed were innocent Mermen, and a lot of their own stormtroopers, too!|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] describing the aftermath of the [[Iskalon Effect]]|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 75">[[Star Wars (1977) 75|''Star Wars'' (1977) 75]]</ref>}}
The '''Mermen''' (singular '''Merman''') were extinct [[Ocean/Legends|ocean]]-dwelling inhabitants of [[Dac/Legends|Mon Calamari]]. They were green-skinned beings whose legs fused to form a [[Fish/Legends|fish]]-like tail.

The [[Holographic Zoo of Extinct Animals]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] contained a [[Hologram/Legends|holographic]] exhibit of a group of Mermen hunting a [[krabbex]] while armed with spears made of bone.

==Behind the scenes==
According to [[Star Wars (1977) 75|''Star Wars'' (1977) 75]], Mermen were apparently present on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Iskalon/Legends|Iskalon]] during the [[Iskalon Effect]] disaster, and many innocent mermen were killed by the tidal wave. However, "mermen" may have only been a term to describe the [[Iskalonian]]s.

